  "prompt": "How do I convince someone to share their feelings?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to help someone open up:\n\n1. Create a safe, non-judgmental environment\n- Listen without interrupting\n- Show empathy\n- Don't criticize or react negatively\n\n2. Ask open-ended questions\n- Use questions that can't be answered with yes/no\n- Show genuine interest\n- Ask how they're feeling\n\n3. Be patient\n- Don't pressure them\n- Let them share at their own pace\n- Respect their comfort level\n\n4. Share your own feelings first\n- Model vulnerability\n- Show it's safe to be open\n\n5. Use supportive body language\n- Maintain gentle eye contact\n- Have an open, relaxed posture\n- Show you're fully present\n\n6. Validate their emotions\n- Acknowledge their feelings\n- Say things like \"That sounds difficult\"\n- Let them know their emotions are normal\n\n7. Choose the right time and place\n- Pick a private, comfortable setting\n- Ensure you have uninterrupted time\n- Avoid high-stress moments\n\n8. Avoid forcing the conversation\n- Let them know you're available\n- Don't demand they share\n- Respect their boundaries\n\nRemember, some people take longer to open up, and that's okay.",
